						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in front of the Chennakēśavasvāmi village.</p>						

						<p>UTTAMĀDITYA CHŌḺA MAHĀRĀJA.</p>						

						<p>8th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription can be assigned to the second quarter of 8th century A.D. on the basis of palaeography and internal evidences.</p>						

						<p>Slightly damaged. Records the gift of a <hi rend="italic">pannavīsa</hi> to a brāhmin <hi rend="italic">(pāṟa)</hi> Chediśa(r*) ma of Kōsiya <hi rend="italic">(i.e., Kauśika gōtra)</hi> propably by the king Uttamāditya. It is stated to have been composed <hi rend="italic">(vrāsiri)</hi> by Erama, a brāhmin <hi rend="italic">(pāṟa)</hi> and engraved by Kuṇandāḷuvaṉṟu. Eyarikalli Kulagaṭṭuḍlu, Vendarambu Vēnavōjaṉṟu are the witnesses for the gift.</p>						

						<p>(Pub. <hi rend="italic">Epigraphia Indica.</hi> Vol. XXVII, pp 240 ff.)</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
